#: ../../../source/docs/porting/connecting_cpp_and_javascript/WebIDL-Binder.rst:5
msgid "WebIDL Binder"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/connecting_cpp_and_javascript/WebIDL-Binder.rst:7
msgid ""
"The *WebIDL Binder* provides a simple and lightweight approach to binding C+"
"+, so that compiled code can be called from JavaScript as if it were a "
"normal JavaScript library."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/connecting_cpp_and_javascript/WebIDL-Binder.rst:9
msgid ""
"The *WebIDL Binder* uses `WebIDL <http://www.w3.org/TR/WebIDL/>`_ to define "
"the bindings, an interface language that was *specifically designed* for "
"gluing together C++ and JavaScript. Not only is this a natural choice for "
"the bindings, but because it is low-level it is relatively easy to optimize."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/connecting_cpp_and_javascript/WebIDL-Binder.rst:11
msgid ""
"The binder supports the subset of C++ types that can be expressed in WebIDL. "
"This subset is more than sufficient for most use cases — examples of "
"projects that have been ported using the binder include the `Box2D <https://"
"github.com/kripken/box2d.js/#box2djs>`_ and `Bullet <https://github.com/"
"kripken/ammo.js/#ammojs>`_ physics engines."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/connecting_cpp_and_javascript/WebIDL-Binder.rst:13
msgid ""
"This topic shows how bind and use C++ classes, functions and other types "
"using IDL."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/connecting_cpp_and_javascript/WebIDL-Binder.rst:15
msgid ""
"An alternative to the *WebIDL Binder* is to use :ref:`Embind`. For more "
"information see :ref:`interacting-with-code-binding-cpp`."
msgstr ""

