#: ../../../source/docs/porting/connecting_cpp_and_javascript/WebIDL-Binder.rst:274
msgid ""
"This will generate a ``get_numericalConstant()`` method in the bindings, but "
"not a corresponding setter. The attribute will also be defined as read-only "
"in JavaScript, meaning that trying to set it will have no effect on the "
"value, and will throw an error in strict mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/connecting_cpp_and_javascript/WebIDL-Binder.rst:276
msgid ""
"It is possible for a return type to have multiple specifiers. For example, a "
"method that returns a constant reference would be marked up in the IDL using "
"``[Ref, Const]``."
